HEADWORD: Autopsy
<hw>Au"top*sy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
seen by one's self; <?/ self + <?/ seen: cf. F. <ets>autopsie</ets>. See
<er>Optic</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Personal
observation or examination; seeing with one's own eyes; ocular
view.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By <qex>autopsy</qex> and experiment.</q>
<rj><qau>Cudworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Dissection of a dead body, for the
purpose of ascertaining the cause, seat, or nature of a disease; a
post-mortem examination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

